    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf there is a plugin that has error when being added, any plugins following will also not be added, which can break users workflow\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\n---@file minimal.lua\n\nvim.opt.packpath:append(vim.fn.stdpath('data') .. '/site')\n\nlocal github = function(name)\n\treturn 'https://github.com/' .. name\nend\n\nvim.pack.add {\n\t{\n\t\tsrc = github 'nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter',\n\t\tversion = 'main'\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\tsrc = github 'nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter-textobjects',\n\t\tversion = 'master'\n\t},\n\tgithub 'neovim/nvim-lspconfig'\n}\n```\n\n1. nvim --clean -u repro.lua\n=> You can see a screen full of error, which is very expected (or intentional). But the real bug I want to report is in next step\n2. `:echo nvim_list_runtime_paths()`\n=> You can see `nvim-treesitter` and `nvim-treesitter-textobjects` already included in rtp, but not `nvim-lspconfig`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`nvim-lspconfig` should be added even though there is an error when adding `nvim-treesitter-textobjects`.\n\nI think the function `pack_add` in file `$VIMRUNTIME/lua/vim/pack.lua` or the command `vim.cmd.packadd()` used in that function should be guarded with `pcall()`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-cbfc3d1cdc\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNA\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNA\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nNA\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nNA\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom source",
